The Fremont: 1 bed/1 bath (627 sq. ft.)<br>
Our Fremont units come newly remodeled with quartz countertops, hardwood-style vinyl plank flooring and a full suite of brand-new appliances including a washer/dryer, dishwasher, built-in microwave, self-cleaning oven, and a refrigerator. <br>
You will have plenty of cabinet space with all-adjustable shelving and a built-in cutting board. The kitchen opens into a spacious living area and the extra-large sliding door allows for great light and ventilation. You'll have a private storage on your covered patio/deck, great for use in all seasons! <br>
These apartments lease quickly, so call one of the friendly leasing specialists today and do not forget to ask about the current specials!<br>
Location is everything. At your doorstep you'll find TriMet and light rail services to Hillsboro, Beaverton, downtown Portland, and the Portland International Airport. Situated in a quiet residential setting, the lively shops and restaurants of Orenco Station along with the streets of Tanasbourne are only moments away. The Hillsboro Library is literally right around the corner, while the streams, waterfalls and paved paths of Dawson Parks are only a short walk away. <br>
At Commons at Hawthorn Village, you can indulge in the luxuries of urban-style living without the urban streets. Enjoy the lush greens of our resort-style grounds. Unwind in the seasonally heated pool, soothing year-round spa, or relaxing cedar-lined sauna. The condo-style apartments offer open kitchen/living areas, and some even feature vaulted ceilings and fireplaces! With a wide variety of floor plans, you will surely find Commons at Hawthorn Village to be a luxurious place to live.<br>
Online payments and maintenance request accepted along with 24-hour emergency maintenance.<br>
Commons at Hawthorn Village has a $350.00 security deposit (on approved credit) or equal to one month's rent due with-in 24 hours of getting your approval phone call. Pro-rated rent is due on move in day- to get your keys!<br>
Two full grown cats or dogs less than 50 lbs. per apartment is welcome. An additional security deposit of $400.00 is required along with $30 a month pet rent per pet. Water/Sewer charge: 1 bedroom: $60.00, 2 bedroom: $68.00, 3 bedroom: $78.00 per month, paid with rent. Trash: 1 bedrooms owe $5.00, 2 bedrooms owe $7.00 and 3 bedrooms owe $10.00 per month.<br>
An $18 application fee must be paid, and a thorough background check must be conducted for every adult staying on property.<br>
Commons at Hawthorn Village is owned and managed by Tandem Property Management, Inc.<br>
Contact one of our professional leasing staff at  <a href="#" class="show-contact" title="click to show contact info" data-href="/reply/pdx/apa/7516967706/__SERVICE_ID__" rel="nofollow">show contact info</a>
 for more information about this wonderful home and the current specials. OR visit our website at https://www.commonsathawthornvillage.com to view more floor plans, photos, and more information. <br>
**Pricing, lease terms, and specials are subject to change at any time. **<br>
